  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     CNN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Convolutional filters detect spatial features hierarchically
Year:        1989
Researchers: LeCun et al.
Applications:Image classification, object detection
Related:     Pooling, feature maps, ResNet

Concept:     Gradient Descent
Category:    Optimization
Definition:  Iteratively adjusts parameters to minimize loss function
Year:        1847
Researchers: Cauchy; ML by many
Applications:Training all ML models
Related:     SGD, Adam, momentum, learning rate

Concept:     RAG
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Combines retrieval from knowledge base with generative model
Year:        2020
Researchers: Lewis et al.
Applications:QA, chatbots, enterprise AI
Related:     Vector database, semantic search, LLM

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Categorical Imperative
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Act only on principles you could will to be universal laws
Philosopher:  Immanuel Kant
Example:      Don't lie; if universal lying existed, language would break down

